{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Finish Jira hard-delete -> outbound re-create (replaces lost epic-3e36)\n\n## Why\nOn a Jira hard-delete the reconciler preserves local content (ADR 0027/0028) BUT never re-creates the Jira\nissue — a `follow_on` re-create payload IS built (`apply_inbound.py:553-558`, key `action=\"create_after_hard_delete\"`)\nbut never consumed, and the branch writes a COMMENT falsely claiming it was emitted. Finish the feature.\nCitations: `apply_inbound.py:541-560`; `applier.py:469-471` (consumer only handles `kind==\"suppress_pair\"`).\n\n## What (consume the EXISTING follow-on shape — no new key invented)\n1. Key mismatch: `_apply_inbound_delete` branches on `payload.get(\"probe_outcome\")` but the prod probe router\n   emits `reason`. CANONICAL = `reason`: update the branch to read `reason`; update BOTH affected unit-test\n   fixtures (`test_inbound_leaf_bodies.py:333` redirect branch AND the hard_delete case) to match.\n2. The existing follow-on already uses `action=\"create_after_hard_delete\"` with the preserved local fields.\n   Do NOT invent a `kind=` sentinel — CONSUME the existing `action=\"create_after_hard_delete\"` dict.\n3. Consumer wiring: in `applier.py:469-471`, add a branch for `action==\"create_after_hard_delete\"` that\n   `bind_pending(local_id)` (write-ahead) then routes through `dispatch_one.create_one` (JQL dedup + `bind_confirm`)\n   — NOT `_apply_outbound_create` (no dedup/binding). The payload carries the `fields` dict create_one needs\n   (title/description/priority/status/assignee, labels) from the preserved local ticket. Injection: create_one is\n   invoked directly by this consumer branch (it is its own dispatch), so there is NO separate \"prepend to\n   outbound batch before _apply_batch\" step — that earlier phrasing is removed to avoid the contradiction.\n4. Idempotency: create_one's JQL dedup + `recover_pending_bindings` prevent double-create on retry; if create_one\n   itself fails (API 5xx/timeout/budget), it records a per-mutation failure and the next pass retries (dedup binds\n   to the existing issue if the create partially succeeded) — add tests for both partial-failure directions.\n5. Stale-binding lifecycle (corrected): `bind_confirm(local_id, new_key)` ADDS `reverse[new_key]=local_id` and\n   sets `bindings[local_id]=new_key`, but it does NOT remove the dead `reverse[old_key]` entry. Explicitly delete\n   the stale `reverse[old_key]` (and any `bindings[local_id]==old_key` staleness) in the same save. Add a test\n   asserting local_id ends bound to new_key AND `reverse` has no entry for old_key.\n6. Guard: only genuine `hard_delete` re-creates (redirect/out_of_window/trash do NOT); guard test.\n7. Observability: log create + rebind success/failure. Fix the misleading COMMENT.\n8. Repoint `TODO(epic-3e36)` (apply_inbound.py:560) to THIS epic; clear `.joe-janitor/report-2026-07-02.md:137`.\n\n## Scope\n`apply_inbound.py` (reason key + preserve existing action follow-on), `applier.py` (consumer branch +\nbind_pending + create_one route + reverse-entry cleanup), `dispatch_one.py` (via existing create_one), tests.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Canonical `reason` key; BOTH redirect + hard_delete unit-test fixtures updated; hard_delete branch reachable in the real dispatch path.\n- [ ] Existing `action=\"create_after_hard_delete\"` follow-on consumed at `applier.py:469-471` via `bind_pending`+`create_one` (dedup+bind_confirm); payload supplies create_one's `fields`.\n- [ ] Idempotent: retry after either partial-failure direction (create ok/rebind fails; create fails) does not double-create (tests).\n- [ ] After re-create, local_id bound to NEW key AND stale `reverse[old_key]` removed in the same save (test).\n- [ ] Only genuine hard-deletes re-create (guard test); create/rebind logged; COMMENT accurate; `TODO(epic-3e36)` repointed; janitor flag cleared.\n- [ ] End-to-end test: inbound hard-delete -> outbound re-create in one pass.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783478491363577001,"uuid":"800b0664-5373-45ed-a55c-eba26dc0e840"}